# YouTube API Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
To expand the functionality of the Django YouTube integration by adding endpoints that perform full CRUD operations and retrieve data. This allows the frontend to manage a user's YouTube channel comprehensively as part of the social media marketing tool.

## Proposed Changes
We will update [youtube_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Sindhuja65/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/youtube_backend/youtube/services/youtube_service.py) to wrap YouTube Data API calls and [views.py](file:///c:/Users/Sindhuja65/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/youtube_backend/youtube/views.py) to expose these as Django REST Framework endpoints.

### [youtube/services/youtube_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Sindhuja65/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/youtube_backend/youtube/services/youtube_service.py)
Add the following methods:
- `get_channel_details()`: Fetch information about the authenticated user's channel.
- `get_videos(limit=50)`: Fetch the list of videos uploaded by the user.
- `update_video(video_id, title, description)`: Update the metadata of an existing video.
- `delete_video(video_id)`: Delete a video from the channel.

### [youtube/views.py](file:///c:/Users/Sindhuja65/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/youtube_backend/youtube/views.py)
Expose the service methods as API endpoints:
- `YoutubeChannelView(APIView)`: GET to fetch channel details.
- `YoutubeVideosView(APIView)`: GET to fetch a list of uploaded videos.
- `YoutubeVideoDetailView(APIView)`: 
    - PUT/PATCH to update video metadata.
    - DELETE to remove a video.

### [youtube/urls.py](file:///c:/Users/Sindhuja65/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/youtube_backend/youtube/urls.py)
Register the new endpoints:
- `/youtube/channel/`
- `/youtube/videos/`
- `/youtube/videos/<video_id>/`

## Walkthrough & Client Guide
After completion, I will generate an artifact `walkthrough.md` that acts as a guide explaining:
1. What data elements clients need to provide for each action.
2. How the endpoints correspond to the YouTube API lifecycle.
3. Examples of making requests to these new endpoints.
